commitResults.messageTitle: Completed Automated Testing can add more edge cases for bug fixing in the future
Added functions to allow saving in the hard disk and loading from it.
Stored deadline dates as java LocalDateTime
Abstracted more classes, Parser, TaskList, UI and Storage
Organized the classes into package duke and duke.task
Fixed bug for level-7 saving file in data. Added code to check for whether the file exists and to create it if it doesn't exist.
Added JUnit tests for all methods in Parser.java class. Other classes mostly have void methods, not sure whether possible and how to test.
Changed the packages to seedu.duke instead of just duke and created the duke.jar file.
Adjusted coded to comply with coding standards.
Added find function to duke, and fixed bug of deleting, marking or unmarking tasks that are not in the list. Dealing with task numbers that are invalid.
Used Java assertions to define assumptions about the program state.
commitResults.messageBody:
Added assertions in Parser class to define the assumption that empty
inputs will not be passed to the functions in Parser class to be parsed.

Added assertions in TaskList class to define the assumption that the
task number has to be a valid array index, more than or equals to 0.

Added assertions in Task, Event and Deadline classes to define the
assumption that the task number has to be more than or equals to 1.

Improved readability by deleting dead code and redundant variables.

Made the happy path prominent by using guard clauses at the top of the
function and throwing an exception if it enters the guard clause.

Minimized code duplication and edited my comments to be in the format of
writing to a reader.

With this new extension, users can edit their task details by
running a command in this format:
update <taskNum> /<desc/from/to/by> <newInfo>

Added methods in Parser class to parse this new command, as well as
methods in TaskList, Storage, Task, Deadline and Event classes to
support this new extension.

If the user tries to update a non-existent attribute for a task
(e.g updating a /by attribute for a todo task), a DukeException
will be thrown and printed in the DialogBox.

commitResults.messageTitle: Improving code quality by reducing code duplication.
commitResults.messageBody:
Removed changeMarking method in Storage as it functions the same
way as updateFile method in Storage.

commitResults.messageTitle: A-BetterGui Modified fxml files to improve GUI of Bobby.
commitResults.messageBody:
Added background fill colours for user and Bobby's dialog box.

Added anchors to ensure that the window can be resized with the content
being resized nicely as well.

Clipped the image view with Circle shape so that the the user and
bobby's image looks more aesthetically pleasing.

Also modified the code logic to ensure that the data file to store the
task information is properly created if it does not exist when first
initialised.

commitResults.messageBody:
Edited Bobby's responses to sound more friendly.

Renamed all Duke names to Bobby respectively.

Handled the error cases for the extension function, C-Update.

Handled the error where the user states a task number bigger than the
size of the task list. (invalid task number) Also handled the error
when the user does not state the attribute to update and indicate with
"/" character. Handled these error cases by throwing BobbyException.

Updated the readme to introduce Bobby as well as how to use it.

Also added references in my code to give credit to the original authors.

Edited to ensure that all instances of Duke name is replaced with
Bobby instead, in comments, documentation and also the file name of
the text file used to store the information of the tasks on the
hard disk.
